# Monorepo Architecture

## Package Boundaries

- Each package/app must have its own `package.json` with explicit dependencies
- Never import from another package's internal files — only from its public entry point
- Shared code lives in dedicated `packages/` (e.g. `packages/shared`, `packages/ui`)

```
✅ import { Button } from '@org/ui';
❌ import { Button } from '../../packages/ui/src/components/Button';
```

## Workspace Structure

```
apps/           → Deployable applications (web, api, mobile)
packages/       → Shared libraries (ui, utils, config, types)
tools/          → Build scripts, generators, CI helpers
```

- Each package owns its own tests, types, and config
- Root `package.json` handles workspace orchestration only (no app logic)

## Dependency Direction

- `apps/` → `packages/` (allowed)
- `packages/` → `packages/` (allowed, but avoid circular refs)
- `packages/` → `apps/` (forbidden)
- Leaf packages should have zero internal dependencies when possible

## Cross-Package Changes

- Changes spanning multiple packages require a single PR with clear scope per package
- If a shared package changes its public API, update all consumers in the same PR
- Use `workspace:*` protocol for internal dependencies
